      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Erich Schön (later name Kulka) a Czech-Israeli writer and historian. In 1939
          he was arrested by the Gestapo, later he was imprisoned in several concentration camps
          (Dachau, Sachsenhausen, Auschwitz). In the protocol he describes the fate and murder of
          Jacob Edelstein and his family in Auschwitz. Edelstein was the former Elder of the Jewish
          Council in the Theresienstadt ghetto. Testimony of Schön became a part of the
          Documentation campaign, Prague.</p>
      </abstract>




